posts.subject: Do you believe in god pol?
posts.body:
I have always considered myself an atheist; This fundamental divide, honestly, has played a huge role in driving me to hold the political dispositions that I do. I see the world in a matter of material surroundings. Nothing more nothing less.
There is no moral landscape or anything of the sort. There is only material reality.
Because of this I have always considered myself a socialist, Marxist, what have you.

That being said, the question of "whether or not god exists" has always perturbed me, because, if god did exist then I would have to drastically alter my political perception in order to be in line with the teaching of a perceived god.

So, rather than just boxing my self off in my own little echo chamber; I'm coming to /pol/ to get what y'all take is on the existence of god.

Hit me with your best shot.
